rategies and approaches to succeed. This includes the adoption of digital platforms such as ecommerce, social media and mobile enabled tools to continually elevate customer experience. In addition, new business models have emerged to address growing pains, particularly in inventory issues, over manufacturing and sustainability. Brands today are forced to adopt evolution through innovation that is anchored by new values without compromising their DNA. Based on in-depth research and interviews with CEOs from leading luxury companies, Lojacono and Pan show how companies can hedge their risks and remain resilient in times of change.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 01. Dez 2022) 0aLuxury goods industry. 0aOrganizational resilience. 4aBusiness Models. 4aDigital Transformation. 4aLuxussegment. 4aLuxussektor. 4aResilienz. 7aBUSINESS & ECONOMICS / Management.2bisacsh  aB4I.  aBocconi University.  aBocconi for Innovation.  aBusiness Models.  aDe Gruyter.  aDigital Transformation.  aEMiLUX.  aExecutive Masters in Luxury Management.  aGabriella Lojacono.  aInternational Strategy.  aLaura Ru Yun Pan.  aLuxury Management.  aMBA.  aResilience.  aSDA Bocconi School of Management.  aexecutive students.  aluxury brand change.  aluxury brand resillience.  aluxury brand strategy.  aluxury brand streategies.  aluxury brand.  aluxury brands.  amasters students.  aresillience of luxury brands.  aresillience of luxury companies.1 aRu Yun Pan, Laura, eauthor.4aut4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/aut08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Ebook Package English 2021z978311075072008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDG Plus DeG Package 2021 Part 1z978311075070608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEBOOK PACKAGE Business and 